    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a medium model risk assessment. The single deficiency in Test conditions (achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is acknowledged; however, the overall body of evidence, including agreement across two independent laboratories and E/uval values well within acceptance bounds for all three QoIs, supports acceptance of the FEA modeling framework for the stated COU. The credibility assessment team concludes that the simulation evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory submission.",
